  "text": "Considering the high sampling rate at the first stage of the decimation filter, a slink filter is preferred with a large decimation ratio and a low circuit complexity. It has the advantage of being multiplier free and the shifted downsampler in between the accumulators and differencers enable the filter to operate at rates lower than the input rate. The order of the slink filter is determined with respect to the order of the modulator used. The decimator gain should roll-off faster than the modulation noise rises, which necessitates the use of order slink filter following an order modulator [CITATION_1] . A higher order filter will cause additional droop in the in-band magnitude response. Therefore, a 4 th order slink filter with decimation factor of 32 was designed. The z-domain transfer function of the aforementioned filter is given in (1) and the corresponding magnitude response is given in Fig. 4 (a) [CITATION_2] .",
